<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Aloysia</i> <i>wrightii</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> spp., <i>Ephedra</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Pericome</i> <i>caudata</i> or other shrubs occur at sparse cover . The shrub layer can have a variety of other plants including <i>Agave</i> <i>utahensis</i>, <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i>, <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>salsola</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>hymenelytra</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>bigelovii</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> spp., <i>Fouquieria</i> <i>splendens</i>, <i>Grayia</i> <i>spinosa</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i> and <i>Nicotiana</i> <i>obtusifolia</i>. Grasses and forbs, if present, include <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>hymenoides</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>rubens</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> spp., <i>Mentzelia</i> spp. and <i>Phacelia</i> spp. Lichens are predominant lifeform in most areas. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  The shrub layer is sparse. The herbaceous layer is typically sparse; lichen and/or moss can be abundant. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Steep slopes, cliffs, rocky outcrops, eroded hills, lava fields. Substrates are rocky or skeletal thin gravelly soils, derived from various substrates including basalt, conglomerate, gneiss, and sedimentary (gypsum). Textures include sand to silty clay.  </div>
</div>

		
